Debug logging is controlled by the `DEBUG` environment variable. Here's how to enable it:

```
DEBUG=1
```

The logger checks `process.env.DEBUG === "1"` and sets the log level to `"debug"` when true, otherwise it defaults to `"info"`.

So you can enable debug logging by running your app with `DEBUG=1`:

```bash
DEBUG=1 npm start
# or
DEBUG=1 node index.js
```
